isease, if in fact health risks did exist. Morbid obesity as we know it today may simply not have been possible without the modern diet, and modern society/technology to provide an endless supply of easy to reach, unhealthy, addictive food.<\/p>\n","answer_id":45421,"question_id":45416,"up_vote_count":0}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/45416/evolution-to-store-limited-fat","last_activity_date":1461183428,"creation_date":1461171431,"answer_count":1,"title":"Evolution to store limited Fat","body":"<p>Why are our bodies not evolved to store only limited amounts of fat, which won't kill us with all diseases associated with obesity?\nWouldn't obese people die faster and clean the gene pool for people who are slim?<\/p>\n","question_id":45416,"tags":["human-biology","evolution"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":46,"up_vote_count":0,"last_edit_date":1461182113},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4ce918b1ee86a35bf1d21fcfb589f99c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1640,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1640/dermot-harnett","reputation":380,"display_name":"Dermot Harnett"},"score":1,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"score":0,"post_id":45420,"edited":false,"creation_date":1461183712,"comment_id":79538,"body":"+1 Oh..ok! This is a little disturbing to me. The concept of IBD depends on an arbitrary time in the past beyond which if coalescence occurs, then we still call the two alleles IBS (Identical 