iction sites. Howevever, with a system like Gateway cloning, I can define boundary limits to bp resolution by simply desining an appropriate primer.<\/p>\n\n<p>Is my reasoning here correct? I need to justify my choises for experimental design to researchers, so want to make sure I'm being efficient and logical.<\/p>\n","question_id":45358,"tags":["genetics","cloning","protein-expression"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":10,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b36565da21c47f7ee6a791febab27b0a?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":23318,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/23318/asmaa","reputation":6,"display_name":"Asmaa"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":0,"post_id":45368,"edited":false,"creation_date":1461072617,"comment_id":79420,"body":"I don&#39;t think gametes are ever produced by mitosis. There can be modified meiosis in which there is no halving of the number of chromosomes. This can be seen in haploid organisms such as male honeybees."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/kIqWF.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19099,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19099/another-homo-sapien","reputation":1004,"display_name":"another 'Homo sapien'"},"score":0,"post_id":45368,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"edited":false,"creation_date":1461074045,"comment_id":79425,"body":"@WYSIWYG correct, but it is so because male honey bees are produced by parthenogenesis. So all cells in them are haploid and can