disposition of the components of photosystem II. Hence an electochemical gradient is established that can be used for generating the ATP needed for photosynthesis.<\/p>\n","answer_id":45396,"question_id":35632,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/35632/where-do-the-h-ions-come-from-in-light-reactions","last_activity_date":1461100767,"creation_date":1435583917,"answer_count":1,"title":"Where do the H+ ions come from in light reactions?","body":"<p>In the light-dependent reactions of photosynthesis, H<sup>+<\/sup> ions pass to the thylakoid space. Where do these protons come from?<\/p>\n","question_id":35632,"tags":["molecular-biology","metabolism","photosynthesis"],"score":3,"down_vote_count":1,"is_answered":true,"view_count":211,"up_vote_count":4,"last_edit_date":1435586188},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f86edcdb41b1251ce63699ebaa5f5e55?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":19072,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19072/user4050","reputation":101,"display_name":"user4050"},"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/39130/compare-wood-density-at-different-moisture-content-and-conversion","last_activity_date":1461095043,"creation_date":1443461294,"answer_count":0,"title":"Compare wood density at different moisture content and conversion","body":"<p>Say I have a measurement of wood density g/$cm^3$ measure at a certain moisture content, say 12%, and I want to know the equivalent wood density at 15% moisture content.<\/p>\n\n<p>Is there a specific rule to apply?<\/p>\n","question_id":39130,"tags":["trees"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":13,"up_vote_count":0,"last_edit_date":1461089273},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/39b7eb876a5036084ea54aecc1b888b1?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3338,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3338/rrs-ghost","reputation":170,"display_name":"RRs