hondria and therefore mitochondrial genomic DNA.  Mature RBCS (at least in most mammals) <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21698761\" rel=\"nofollow\">do not have mitochondria<\/a>, so the safest answer is probably b) Mature RBC.  <\/p>\n","answer_id":45232,"question_id":45218,"up_vote_count":5,"last_edit_date":1460667906},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5ad3e7ee10a826ac38a6c0f9483b526d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":23312,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/23312/abcd","reputation":67,"display_name":"Abcd"},"score":0,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/kIqWF.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19099,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19099/another-homo-sapien","reputation":1004,"display_name":"another 'Homo sapien'"},"score":0,"post_id":45362,"edited":false,"creation_date":1461065128,"comment_id":79397,"body":"Please add detail and references in your answer or it is likely to be removed soon. What do you mean by &quot;diffused&quot;? Is it about diffusion of gases or diffusion of cells?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":0,"post_id":45362,"edited":false,"creation_date":1461067760,"comment_id":79404,"body":"This does not provide an answer to the question. Once you have sufficient <a href=\"http://biology.stackexchange.com/help/whats-reputation\">reputation<\/a> you will be able to <a href=\"http://biology.stackexchange.com/help/privileges/comment\">comment on any post<\/a>; instead, <a href=\"http://meta.stackexchange.com/questions/214173/why-do-i-need-50-reputation-to-comment-what-can-i-do-instead\">provide answers that don&#39;t require clarification from the asker<\/a>. - <a href=\"/review/low-qu