ith one another.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n<p>Catch: whilst this provides spacial information, you can't get a picture of temporal information: <em>i.e<\/em> you know what is interacting, but not when nor for how long.<\/p>\n","answer_id":43801,"question_id":43681,"up_vote_count":5,"last_edit_date":1456920468}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/43681/how-can-i-make-a-protein-interaction-protein-complex-network","last_activity_date":1460964286,"creation_date":1456438783,"answer_count":1,"title":"How can I make a protein interaction/protein-complex network?","body":"<p>Let's say I have a list of proteins ID. I would like to know whether I can find any complex based on that list. Any example, explanation is appreciated.<\/p>\n\n<p>An example input is what you see below. What can I do with the following list of protein IDs? These IDs are from human. <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>P41182,P56524, P41182,Q9UQL6, P41182,Q8WUI4,Q92793,Q09472,Q9Y6Q9,Q92831\n<\/code><\/pre>\n","question_id":43681,"tags":["bioinformatics","homework","database"],"score":5,"accepted_answer_id":43801,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":98,"up_vote_count":5,"last_edit_date":1460964286},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/7LxPC.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":561,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/561/becko","reputation":503,"display_name":"becko","accept_rate":43},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef567acea1fa50e6645a1c5b3618f12f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":22560,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/22560/grb","reputation":51,"display_name":"Grb"},"score":0,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/7LxPC.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":561,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/561/becko","reputation":503,"display_name":"becko","accept_rate":43},"score":0,"post_id":44360,"edited":false,"creat