ontent come from? I&#39;ve never heard of it and I can&#39;t see how it relates to anything &#39;real&#39; in  genetic information."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Fdh9e.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":23258,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/23258/scient","reputation":71,"display_name":"SciEnt"},"score":0,"post_id":45289,"edited":false,"creation_date":1460920451,"comment_id":79246,"body":"I think I have a solution.. I am only considering 1 strand based on original problem wording, however mdperry I did consider the second strand. I am glad you also brought that up. David the formulas come largely from (<a href=\"https://schneider.ncifcrf.gov/paper/ri/latex/\" rel=\"nofollow\">schneider.ncifcrf.gov/paper/ri/latex<\/a> )  So my soluion"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/ay2bH.gif?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":22057,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/22057/david","reputation":1825,"display_name":"David"},"score":0,"post_id":45289,"edited":false,"creation_date":1460920822,"comment_id":79249,"body":"Thanks @Valentin-Angelo Uzunov. More mathematics than computer science even. I&#39;ll pass on this one."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/56b4833d86d3cccc3ccfd6eeaf0b767e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":14946,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/14946/mdperry","reputation":2645,"display_name":"mdperry"},"score":0,"post_id":45289,"edited":false,"creation_date":1460938068,"comment_id":79265,"body":"So I think you have answered the question yourself. While I am no expert, I think Schneider presents the most thoughtful, and clearest descriptions and explanations in his many publications on this subject. I also appreciate your clarification of the question, and now understand the answers to the points I raised. 14 bits for a 7-mer sounds correct to me.  I don&#39;t really understand what a student is supposed to l