>So 5min delay for <em>E.coli<\/em> is not an issue. (I think this happens to all of us: forgetting to add antibiotic). <\/p>\n","answer_id":23124,"question_id":23122,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1460782526}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/23122/does-adding-antibiotic-after-5-10-mins-of-innoculation-affect-the-protein-yield","last_activity_date":1460782526,"creation_date":1413350678,"answer_count":1,"title":"Does adding antibiotic after 5-10 mins of innoculation affect the protein yield or growth?","body":"<p>I've asked a lab colleague the same question. She said, it would loosen the bacterial cells in the LB medium and plasmids would come out. Is that true? and why?<\/p>\n","question_id":23122,"tags":["molecular-biology","microbiology","lab-techniques"],"score":1,"accepted_answer_id":23124,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":54,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3363534a62c163bf91814cd024889dd8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":19568,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19568/joel","reputation":118,"display_name":"Joel"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/TSuGp.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19521,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19521/jordi-zambrino","reputation":1024,"display_name":"Jordi Zambrino","accept_rate":83},"score":1,"post_id":45263,"edited":false,"creation_date":1460756906,"comment_id":79157,"body":"Could you provide a link to what you were reading?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3363534a62c163bf91814cd024889dd8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":19568,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19568/joel","reputation":118,"display_name":"Joel"},"score":0,"post_id":45263,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/TSuGp.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19521,"link":"http://biology.sta