in from red blood cells which have been retired. <\/p>\n\n<p>There's also a lot of variation from one sample to the next - 10% seems pretty common here as you can imagine).  What makes faeces so dangerous is the bacterial portion, which can pose quite a health risk. <\/p>\n","answer_id":5704,"question_id":5684,"up_vote_count":5}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/5684/what-is-the-composition-of-human-feces","last_activity_date":1460748234,"creation_date":1357432854,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is the composition of human feces?","body":"<p>Are there any studies or general information on the composition of human feces?<\/p>\n\n<p>I'd specifically like to know the percentage of carbohydrates and amino acids relative to the amount that was ingested in diets of various types and amounts. <\/p>\n\n<p>Any additional facts are also welcome.<\/p>\n","question_id":5684,"tags":["human-biology","nutrition","gastroenterology"],"score":12,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":18631,"up_vote_count":12,"last_edit_date":1357438615},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2550aa98332616362fa07d023da45d40?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":28,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/28/gergana-vandova","reputation":5081,"display_name":"Gergana Vandova","accept_rate":35},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/ay2bH.gif?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":22057,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/22057/david","reputation":1825,"display_name":"David"},"score":0,"post_id":44962,"edited":false,"creation_date":1459979092,"comment_id":78460,"body":"What makes you think this is so? Where did you read it? There is a specific mechanism for termination of translation and release of ribosome subunits. I may be wrong but I see no reason that ribosomes would fall off long mRNAs."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2550aa98332616362fa07d023da45d40